<heading id="D0AF81898977FFAFFF707DFCFD94FD55" bold="true" box="[151,598,655,681]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B92CEAF78977FFAFFF707DFCFD94FD55" bold="true" box="[151,598,655,681]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Key to the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C584D668977FFAFFE7B7DFCFD94FD55" authorityName="Cresson" authorityYear="1926" box="[412,598,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92CEAF78977FFAFFE7B7DFCFD94FD55" bold="true" box="[412,598,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Hoplocheiloma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C342656E8977FFAFFF707DA5FA54F876" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="key">
<keyStep id="30AC2E408977FFAFFF707DA5FA5EFC9D" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph id="8BE736E58977FFAFFF707DA5FA5FFCDA" blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30A995D08977FFAFFF707DA5FA5FFCDA" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
1. Wing distinctly spotted, transverse bands broken up so the wing appears mostly infuscated, with 7 widely separated, clear, circular patches (
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFE8B7D87FE65FCF5" box="[364,423,756,777]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–10" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1829,1852]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-93@7.[151,1436,193,1808]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 6–10. Hoplocheiloma hispaniola new species. 6, head; 7, male left lateral; 8, male terminalia; 9, female abdomen; 10, spermathecae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290091/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Head with only one large seta (inner vertical), other setae reduced or absent (
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFB7D7D87FB16FCF5" box="[1178,1236,756,777]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–10" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1829,1852]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-93@7.[151,1436,193,1808]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 6–10. Hoplocheiloma hispaniola new species. 6, head; 7, male left lateral; 8, male terminalia; 9, female abdomen; 10, spermathecae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290091/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).............................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C584D668977FFAFFC207C62FB88FCDA" authority="Marshall, 2011" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2011" box="[967,1098,785,806]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispaniola" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B92CEAF78977FFAFFC207C62FB88FCDA" box="[967,1098,785,806]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. hispaniola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21F578C8977FFAFFBA87C62FB07FCDA" box="[1103,1221,785,806]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
. 
<collectingCountry id="F34F76758977FFAFFB287C62FA5BFCDA" box="[1231,1433,785,806]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Dominican Republic</collectingCountry>
.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE736E58977FFAFFF707C5DFA5EFC9D" blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30A995D08977FFAFFF707C5DFA5EFC9D" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
- Wing with a broad discal band crossing middle (
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFD557C5DFD38FCBF" box="[690,762,814,835]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="15.[151,263,1420,1443]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,181,1410]" captionTargetId="figure-268@15.[151,1436,181,1411]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Hoplocheiloma perforatum (Enderlein). 22, female habitus, left lateral; 23, spermathecae and associated structures; 24, male terminalia, left lateral; 25, female abdominal apex to show dorsum of oviscape; 26, front of head. Abbreviations: dp—distiphallus; hy—hypandrium; aa—aedeagal apodeme; ep—epandrium; ps—paired spermathecae; ss—single spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290105" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290105/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Head with three large setae (inner vertical, orbital and outer vertical, as in 
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFEF37C3FFE9BFC9D" box="[276,345,844,865]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="15.[151,263,1420,1443]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,181,1410]" captionTargetId="figure-268@15.[151,1436,181,1411]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Hoplocheiloma perforatum (Enderlein). 22, female habitus, left lateral; 23, spermathecae and associated structures; 24, male terminalia, left lateral; 25, female abdominal apex to show dorsum of oviscape; 26, front of head. Abbreviations: dp—distiphallus; hy—hypandrium; aa—aedeagal apodeme; ep—epandrium; ps—paired spermathecae; ss—single spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290105" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290105/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
)......................................................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30AC2E408977FFAFFF707C1AFA5EFC45" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph id="8BE736E58977FFAFFF707C1AFA5EFC82" blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" box="[151,1436,873,894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30A995D08977FFAFFF707C1AFA5EFC82" box="[151,1436,873,894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
2. Notum mostly black, postpronotum contrastingly reddish. Base of oviscape bare and shining dorsomedially (
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFB137C1AFAF8FC82" box="[1268,1338,873,894]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–21" captionStartId="13.[151,263,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-52@13.[151,1436,193,1855]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 17–21. Hoplocheiloma maculosum. 17, male terminalia; 18, male abdominal apex, left; 19, male abdomen segments 1–7; 20, spermathecae; 21, female abdominal apex, dorsal. Abbreviations: hy, hypandrium; ea, ejaculatory apodeme; ep, epandrium; aa, aedeagal apodeme, dp, distiphallus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290101/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
)...... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE736E58977FFAFFF707CF5FA5EFC45" blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30A995D08977FFAFFF707CF5FA5EFC45" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
- Notum entirely orange to orange-brown, sometimes patterned with silvery grey areas. Pruinose area at base of oviscape surrounding oviscape so there is no dorsomedial shining strip (
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFCFA7CD7FCA7FC45" box="[797,869,932,953]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="15.[151,263,1420,1443]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,181,1410]" captionTargetId="figure-268@15.[151,1436,181,1411]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Hoplocheiloma perforatum (Enderlein). 22, female habitus, left lateral; 23, spermathecae and associated structures; 24, male terminalia, left lateral; 25, female abdominal apex to show dorsum of oviscape; 26, front of head. Abbreviations: dp—distiphallus; hy—hypandrium; aa—aedeagal apodeme; ep—epandrium; ps—paired spermathecae; ss—single spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290105" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290105/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
).............................................. 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30AC2E408977FFAFFF707CB2FA59FB3D" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph id="8BE736E58977FFAFFF707CB2FA55FB95" blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30A995D08977FFAFFF707CB2FA55FB95" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
3. Wing mostly infuscated, with discal and preapical dark bands separated by clear strips each made up of three more or less coalesced clear circular areas, circular areas usually separated by pigmentation along the wing veins but both clear and dark bands always reaching hind wing margin; apical infuscation distinct (
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFC9F7C8FFC02FBED" box="[888,960,1020,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–16" captionStartId="12.[151,263,1884,1907]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-38@12.[151,1436,193,1863]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 13–16. Hoplocheiloma maculosum (Loew). 13, live female dorsolateral, Cuba; 14, female, abdomen, thorax, wings; 15, live female anterodorsal, Cuba; 16, head." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290097/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Anterior notopleural seta at most half as long as posterior seta. Membranous parts of abdomen mostly pale, female abdomen with pleural pigmentation mostly restricted to bands on dorsal half (
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFE4A7B45FE31FBB7" box="[429,499,1078,1099]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–16" captionStartId="12.[151,263,1884,1907]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-38@12.[151,1436,193,1863]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 13–16. Hoplocheiloma maculosum (Loew). 13, live female dorsolateral, Cuba; 14, female, abdomen, thorax, wings; 15, live female anterodorsal, Cuba; 16, head." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290097/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
), male abdomen with pigmentation of segment three circling abdomen and preceded and followed by extensive pale areas........................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C584D668977FFAFFC407B27FB43FB95" authority="(Loew)" baseAuthorityName="Loew" box="[935,1153,1108,1129]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculosum">
<emphasis id="B92CEAF78977FFAFFC407B27FBF3FB95" box="[935,1073,1108,1129]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. maculosum</emphasis>
(Loew)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectingCountry id="F34F76758977FFAFFB6D7B27FA91FB95" box="[1162,1363,1108,1129]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Dominican Republic</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F34F76758977FFAFFABA7B27FA51FB95" box="[1373,1427,1108,1129]" name="Cuba" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Cuba</collectingCountry>
.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE736E58977FFAFFF707B02FA59FB3D" blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30A995D08977FFAFFF707B02FA59FB3D" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
- Wing bands separated from one another by straight-sided clear strips; dark preapical band parallel-sided, broadly separated from hind margin of wing; apical infuscation indistinct (
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFCE77BFDFCB7FB5F" box="[768,885,1166,1187]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–12" captionStartId="9.[151,263,1898,1921]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-70@9.[151,1436,193,1877]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 11–12. Hoplocheiloma jamaica new species. 11, female habitus, left lateral; 12, male habitus, left lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290095" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290095/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figs. 11, 12</figureCitation>
). Notopleural setae equal in size. Abdominal membranes more extensively pigmented, ventral part of abdomen largely dark............................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C584D668977FFAFFB5F7BDFFAE0FB3D" authority="Marshall, 2011" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2011" box="[1208,1314,1196,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jamaica" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B92CEAF78977FFAFFB5F7BDFFAE0FB3D" box="[1208,1314,1196,1217]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. jamaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21F578C8977FFAFFACE7BDFFA59FB3D" box="[1321,1435,1196,1217]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30AC2E408977FFAFFF707BBAFA5EFA72" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph id="8BE736E58977FFAFFF707BBAFA5FFAE5" blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30A995D08977FFAFFF707BBAFA5FFAE5" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
4. Head and notum orange-brown, presutural part of scutum patterned with silvery grey areas. Wing with three distinct pigmented bands and an infuscated tip, outer margin of discal and preapical bands concave at middle (
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFBB27B95FB5CFB07" box="[1109,1182,1254,1275]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="15.[151,263,1420,1443]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,181,1410]" captionTargetId="figure-268@15.[151,1436,181,1411]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Hoplocheiloma perforatum (Enderlein). 22, female habitus, left lateral; 23, spermathecae and associated structures; 24, male terminalia, left lateral; 25, female abdominal apex to show dorsum of oviscape; 26, front of head. Abbreviations: dp—distiphallus; hy—hypandrium; aa—aedeagal apodeme; ep—epandrium; ps—paired spermathecae; ss—single spermatheca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290105" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290105/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Hind femur dark at least on basal half, with 1–2 orange distal bands.................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C584D668977FFAFFCBD7A77FBFFFAE5" authority="Cresson." authorityName="Cresson." box="[858,1085,1284,1305]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perforatum">
<emphasis id="B92CEAF78977FFAFFCBD7A77FC21FAE5" box="[858,995,1284,1305]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. perforatum</emphasis>
Cresson.
</taxonomicName>
<collectingCountry id="F34F76758977FFAFFBA57A77FAC9FAE5" box="[1090,1291,1284,1305]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Dominican Republic</collectingCountry>
, maybe 
<collectingCountry id="F34F76758977FFAFFABC7A77FA5AFAE5" box="[1371,1432,1284,1305]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE736E58977FFAFFF707A52FA5EFA72" blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30A995D08977FFAFFF707A52FA5EFA72" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
- Head and notum orange, at least presutural part of scutum without silvery gray pattern. Hind femur usually orange with narrow dark bands (sometimes uniformly orange-brown). Outer margins of discal band convex or more or less straight, preapical band narrow and more or less straight-edged (
<emphasis id="B92CEAF78977FFAFFD8A7A2FFD1FFA8D" box="[621,733,1372,1393]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C584D668977FFAFFD8A7A2FFD1BFA8D" authorityName="Gmelin, 1790:" authorityYear="2850" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[621,729,1372,1393]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="totliana">H. totliana</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFD037A2FFCE8FA8D" box="[740,810,1372,1393]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–35" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1831,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,193,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-96@19.[151,1436,193,1810]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 31–35. Hoplocheiloma totliana (Gmelin). 31, male terminalia; 32, spermathecae and associated structures; 33, live female dorsal, Cuba; 34, female abdominal apex to show dorsum of oviscape; 35, live female left lateral, Cuba." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290111/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
) or coalesced with apical infuscation to form a composite distal band (
<emphasis id="B92CEAF78977FFAFFEFA7A0AFE6FFA72" box="[285,429,1401,1422]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C584D668977FFAFFEFA7A0AFE6BFA72" box="[285,425,1401,1422]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugatum">H. ferrugatum</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFE547A0AFE28FA72" box="[435,490,1401,1422]" captionStart="FIGURES 5" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1745,1768]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,700,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-345@5.[151,1436,700,1724]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5. 5A. Hoplocheiloma ferrugatum Hennig female holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290089" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290089/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
)............................................................................. 5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30AC2E408977FFAFFF707AE5FA5FF9A7" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph id="8BE736E58977FFAFFF707AE5FA5EFA1A" blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30A995D08977FFAFFF707AE5FA5EFA1A" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
5. Wing with discal band sometimes broad but never reaching hind margin of wing, distal band narrow but distinct from apical infuscation (
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFEBB7AC7FE6AFA35" box="[348,424,1460,1481]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–30" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1745,1768]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,434,1728]" captionTargetId="figure-217@17.[151,1436,434,1728]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 27–30. Hoplocheiloma rhytisma new species. 27, female habitus, left lateral; 28, spermathecae and associated structures; 29, male abdomen segments 3–7, right lateral; 30, male terminalia, left lateral. Abbreviations: dp—distiphallus; hy— hypandrium; aa—aedeagal apodeme; ep—epandrium; ps—paired spermathecae (female), pleural sac (male); ss—single spermatheca; gf—genital fork." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290107/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
). Epicephalon and paracephalon dull, paracephalon not conspicuously bulging. Main vertical row of katepisternal setae usually darker than weaker anterior golden row............................................... 6
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE736E58977FFAFFF707A9DFA5FF9A7" blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30A995D08977FFAFFF707A9DFA5FF9A7" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
- Discal band very large, taking up most of wing, broadly reaching hind margin of wing and separated from large apical infuscated area (distal band coalesced with apical infuscation, by a narrow transverse pale area (
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFBA5797FFBBEF9DD" box="[1090,1148,1548,1569]" captionStart="FIGURES 5" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1745,1768]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,700,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-345@5.[151,1436,700,1724]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5. 5A. Hoplocheiloma ferrugatum Hennig female holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290089" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290089/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Epicephalon and paracephalon shining, paracephalon conspicuously bulging (
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFD32795AFCD6F9C2" box="[725,788,1577,1598]" captionStart="FIGURES 5" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1745,1768]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,700,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-345@5.[151,1436,700,1724]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5. 5A. Hoplocheiloma ferrugatum Hennig female holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290089" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290089/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Main vertical row of katepisternal setae golden, same color as weaker anterior golden row............................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C584D668977FFAFFBEF7935FB26F9A7" authority="Hennig." authorityName="Hennig." box="[1032,1252,1606,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugatum">
<emphasis id="B92CEAF78977FFAFFBEF7935FB53F9A7" box="[1032,1169,1606,1627]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. ferrugatum</emphasis>
Hennig.
</taxonomicName>
<collectingCountry id="F34F76758977FFAFFB0E7935FAF0F9A7" box="[1257,1330,1606,1627]" name="Mexico" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="499CF8078977FFAFFAD87935FA50F9A7" box="[1343,1426,1606,1627]" country="Mexico" name="Yucatan" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Yucatan</collectingRegion>
).
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30AC2E408977FFAFFF707917FAB8F8EC" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<paragraph id="8BE736E58977FFAFFF707917FA59F94F" blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30A995D08977FFAFFF707917FA59F94F" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
6. Pleuron with two prominent dark patches covered with silvery pruinosity, one covering the posterior third of the anepisternum and a less distinct one on the upper katepisternum (
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFD3779F2FCDAF96A" box="[720,792,1665,1686]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–30" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1745,1768]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,434,1728]" captionTargetId="figure-217@17.[151,1436,434,1728]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 27–30. Hoplocheiloma rhytisma new species. 27, female habitus, left lateral; 28, spermathecae and associated structures; 29, male abdomen segments 3–7, right lateral; 30, male terminalia, left lateral. Abbreviations: dp—distiphallus; hy— hypandrium; aa—aedeagal apodeme; ep—epandrium; ps—paired spermathecae (female), pleural sac (male); ss—single spermatheca; gf—genital fork." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290107/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
). Discal band more or less circular, widely separated from anterior wing margin and with distal face strongly convex. R 
<subScript id="17DC34A08977FFAFFD3079D8FD2EF94B" attach="both" box="[727,748,1707,1719]" fontSize="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">2+3</subScript>
ending far beyond plane of dm-cu (
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFBA679EDFB41F94F" box="[1089,1155,1694,1715]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,263,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-41@3.[151,1436,195,1859]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Hoplocheiloma dominica new species. 1, male habitus, left lateral; 2, spermathecae and associated structures; 3, female thorax and abdomen, right lateral; 4, male, wing pigmentation." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290085" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290085/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFB6879EDFB6AF94F" box="[1167,1192,1694,1715]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–30" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1745,1768]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,434,1728]" captionTargetId="figure-217@17.[151,1436,434,1728]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 27–30. Hoplocheiloma rhytisma new species. 27, female habitus, left lateral; 28, spermathecae and associated structures; 29, male abdomen segments 3–7, right lateral; 30, male terminalia, left lateral. Abbreviations: dp—distiphallus; hy— hypandrium; aa—aedeagal apodeme; ep—epandrium; ps—paired spermathecae (female), pleural sac (male); ss—single spermatheca; gf—genital fork." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290107/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">27</figureCitation>
).................. 7
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE736E58977FFAFFF7079CDFAB8F8EC" blockId="1.[151,1437,726,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<keyLead id="30A995D08977FFAFFF7079CDFAB8F8EC" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
- Pleuron uniformly orange. Discal band with distal face almost straight, anterior part reaching wing margin (
<figureCitation id="13632A608977FFAFFB1779CDFAFAF92F" box="[1264,1336,1726,1747]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–35" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1831,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,193,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-96@19.[151,1436,193,1810]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 31–35. Hoplocheiloma totliana (Gmelin). 31, male terminalia; 32, spermathecae and associated structures; 33, live female dorsal, Cuba; 34, female abdominal apex to show dorsum of oviscape; 35, live female left lateral, Cuba." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5290111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5290111/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
). R 
<subScript id="17DC34A08977FFAFFABE79B8FAACF92B" attach="left" box="[1369,1390,1739,1751]" fontSize="5" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">2+3</subScript>
ending at or very slightly beyond plane of dm-cu... 
<taxonomicName id="4C584D668977FFAFFD2279ADFC49F90F" authority="(Gmelin)" authorityName="Gmelin, 1790:" authorityYear="2850" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[709,907,1758,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="totliana">
<emphasis id="B92CEAF78977FFAFFD2279ADFCEFF90F" box="[709,813,1758,1779]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. totliana</emphasis>
(Gmelin)
</taxonomicName>
(widely known as 
<taxonomicName id="4C584D668977FFAFFBD979ADFB3BF90F" authority="Steyskal" authorityName="Steyskal" authorityYear="1968" box="[1086,1273,1758,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Hoplocheiloma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fabricii">
